    Religious places in & outside India
    </h1>
    <p>
      Faith is an adhesive that has been binding many people and societies together for ages. Moreover, some people often consider religious places as spiritual milestones while others consider it as a place to let go of all facades and completely surrender. Whatever it may be for you, there are a plethora of religious places in and outside India. With all their eccentricities and similarities, they make up for a perfect place to cover during a family vacation. TravelTriangle takes you to many such locations across the globe. So whether you are starting a new phase of your life on a spiritual note or just eager to pay a visit, mentioned below is a list of religious places that you can visit.
    </p>
    <h2>Top Religious Places Around The World</h2>

    <h3>Nepal</h3>

    <div class="kerala">
      <img src="kerala1.jpg" alt="img" height="150px" width="270px" />
      <img src="kerala2.jpg" alt="img" height="150px" width="270px" />
