      <!-- <img src="goa4.jpeg" alt="img" height="150px" width="270px" /> -->
    </div>

    <p>
      Bali is home to more than 20,000 temples most of which are surrounded with jaw-dropping vistas. Most of Bali temples are stone-carved marvels displaying deities and other eccentric images. A trip to Bali can never be complete without visiting many of its Hindu and Buddhist temples. Some of the most prominent temples of Bali such as Tanah Lot Temple, Uluwatu Temple, Ulun Danu Beratan Temple, Besakih Temple, Goa Gajah, Underwater Temple, Taman Ayun Temple, and Goa Lawah Temple are also the most famous religious places around the world.
    </p>

    <h3>Sri Lanka</h3>

    <div class="kerala">
      <img src="kashmir1.jpeg" alt="img" height="150px" width="270px" />
      <img src="kashmir2.jpeg" alt="img" height="150px" width="270px" />
      <img src="kashmir3.jpeg" alt="img" height="150px" width="270px" />
      <!-- <img src="kashmir4.jpeg" alt="img" height="150px" width="270px" /> -->
    </div>

    <p>
      Sri Lanka is a colorful congregation of Buddhism, Hinduism, Christian, and Zoroastrianism. Therefore, the temples in Sri Lanka also circles the essence of these religions. Moreover, Sri Lankan history is deeply rooted in Indian mythology as well. Therefore, one can also find rare find temples such as Seetha Amman Temple and Sri Munneswaram Devasthanam that as per folklore are linked to the Ramayana era. Some of the must-visit temples of Sri Lanka include Gangaramaya Temple Colombo, Sri Dalada Maligawa, Isipathanaramaya temple, Sri Kailawasanathan Swami Devasthanam, Sri Ponnambalam Vanesar Kovil, Koneswaram temple, and Maviddapuram Kandaswamy Temple.
    </p>

    <h3>Cambodia</h3>

    <div class="kerala">
      <img src="kashmir1.jpeg" alt="img" height="150px" width="270px" />
      <img src="kashmir2.jpeg" alt="img" height="150px" width="270px" />
      <img src="kashmir3.jpeg" alt="img" height="150px" width="270px" />
      <!-- <img src="kashmir4.jpeg" alt="img" height="150px" width="270px" /> -->
    </div>

    <p>
      Cambodia creates astounding imagery and its many temples are just a cherry on the top. Here, you will get to witness the amalgam of Buddhism and Hinduism. Temples here are also one of the most visited religious places in the world. Bayon, Banteay Kdei, Neak Pean, Banteay Srei, and Pre Rup are some of the most prominent temples in Cambodia. Moreover, if there is one temple that you just cannot afford to miss, it is Angkor Wat.
    </p>
    
